According to recent Labor Department statistics, job openings in the United States hit a record high of 7.14 million in August. This indicates a tight labor market and potential inflationary pressures for companies. The total number of hires also reached a new record of 5.78 million. However, the number of workers looking for jobs fell from 6.23 million in August to 5.96 million in September. Workers also showed confidence in the job market, as evidenced by a quits rate of 3.58 million.